                                PrinterGFX

        Although the printer editor will give you control over many aspects
of how the Amiga controls your printer, printing pictures is an entirely
different ball game altogether which is why there's a separate editor
called PrinterGFX. This editor gives you extensive control over how
pictures are printed on your printer. To increase the quality of your
printout, this editor allows you to select a number of different dithering
patterns and you can turn on smoothing which attempts to smooth out the
jagged edges normally associated with bitmapped images.



